{"questionId":"22264","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the equation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>z</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>z</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℂ</mi></math>.&nbsp;The roots of this equation are&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Im</mi><mfenced><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Im</mi><mfenced><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></mfenced><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The roots <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math> are represented by the points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> respectively on an&nbsp;Argand diagram.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Plot the points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> on an Argand diagram.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to express&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;in Cartesian form and translate 1 unit in the&nbsp;positive direction of the real axis<em>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><br>OR</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to express&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>w</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>w</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>w</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;in Cartesian form<em>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:90px;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/bfd6971c69f380348ebf0dd1e9b4193c8bc0634d.png\"></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> To award <em><strong>A</strong></em> marks, it is not necessary to see <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>, the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>w</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>, or&nbsp;the solid lines</p>\n<p><em>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4</strong></em><em><strong>&nbsp;marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22264","referenceCode":"21N.1.AHL.TZ0.12b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Plot the points A, B and C on an Argand diagram.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.12—Complex numbers – Cartesian form and Argand diag","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.13—Polar and Euler form","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Complex roots of polynomials, conjugate roots, De Moivre’s, powers & roots of complex numbers"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}